    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>In art or aesthetics, S-shaped curved lines appearing within an object, as the boundary line of an object, or as a virtual boundary line formed by the composition of several objects. The idea originated with William Hogarth as an essential part of his theory of aesthetics.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
